Dear Jack: 
Your card came a moment ago - just as I was sitting down to my unclear. I want to thank you again for the unclear you w unclear?? faithfully supply me with. The one on T.V. was badly needed. I do wish I had a set at Tunes unclear??, though. Touched that the fellows wonder what I'm up to. The answer is very little. I am now the father of four, and have no job. I swear unclear?? I get by on my writing - you can imagine how well. Have a new collection comin in March, but doubt that I'll be able to retire on the proceeds. Are you doing encyclopedias still? Best to you + Mrs C., Jack. 
- Jim (and Betty).

and she'd never help any friend of Gehman. I told her that she had her facts mixed up -- that I had seen Gehman only once in my life -- but she thought I was lying; and that was that. To hell with the bunch of them. I think my book will be decent without their help; and even if it isn't, I just want to get it finished and forget the whole fucking thing. I'll get it finished up here anyway.
Wish you were here. 
Love, Jim

17 December 1972
Dear Gladys & Jack, 
No cards this year. I'm not up to my annual trip to the National Gallery in Dublin for a stack of madonnas, I've got springs of cowardice which have barely been tapped. I went back ot the U.S. this summer on family business, and every plane was certainly an ordeal. The only ones who didn't [underlined] search everywhere were Aer Lingus in Dublin, and I gather that that has since been rectified. Our greengrocer, a very respectable looking woman, even had her hair searched.
Nothing happens here, which in some ways is just as well. Our eldest has, at 25, returned to college, her sophomore year, this time at the U. of Mass in Boston. The other four are here, waiting for some sort of sign in the skies to indicate the way, I gather. 
Jim is working, so non-stop that he said he wouldn't be able to get any cards out at all this year, so I am stepping into the breach. I hope things are fine in Moberly, Mo, whatever they are in the rest of the world. Maybe you have got it made. (We had until a few years ago. Greystones is getting elephantiasis.) Merry Christmas & Happy New Year.
signed Betty
